Dear Pablo,

--- REGARDING "a" AS A PREPOSITION:

I hope I did this correctly; I had to go two generations, from 1011 to 1013, to make it work.
(The new compiler feature is in the intermediate 1012, but changes to El Seso, that use that feature,
cannot be compiled by the 1012, so they have to wait for the 1013 El Seso. Confusing, I know.)

Anyway:

"Adjuntar el byte del evento después de la cadena del texto." is now "Adjuntar el byte del evento a la cadena del texto."

"Adjuntar la consulta después de la URL." is now "Adjuntar la consulta a la URL."

"Adjuntar el trabajo después de los trabajos." is now "Adjuntar el trabajo a los trabajos."

--- REGARDING BOXES:

Caja is in, cuadro is out. El Seso, Sal Monet, and Sal Monet Instructions updated.
We can make "cuadro" a synonym later, but caja (as of now) will appear in the documentation.

--- REGARDING "a lenguaraz"

\An alternative connotation [of "una lenguaraz"] is a shameless chatterer. 
Funny.

\SAL la lenguaraz, great!
Perhaps you can use that in the title of your a paper for the VIII Congreso Internacional de la Lengua Española.

Tu amigo,
Gerry

